<title>Charles Lucien Lambert, Sr., African American Composer & Pianist</title>
<meta name="description" content="Charles Lucien Lambert, Sr. (c.1828-1896) was an African American composer and pianist born in New Orleans. Racism caused him to leave for France by 1854 .He enjoyed success there and later in Brazil, starting in the 1860s.  He had a music store and taught music to, among others, the great Brazilian composer Ernesto Nazareth.">
<meta name="keywords" content="African American composer, African American pianist, exile, France, Brazil, Ernesto Nazareth, New Orleans, racism">
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 6.0">
<meta name="ProgId" content="FrontPage.Editor.Document">
<meta name="Microsoft Theme" content="none">
<meta name="Microsoft Border" content="none, default">
</head>

